text: Eline Olga Coene (born 11 April 1964) is a Dutch badminton player. She competed in women's singles and women's doubles at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona, and in women's doubles at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1964 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch female badminton players Category:Olympic badminton players of the Netherlands Category:Badminton players at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Badminton players at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:People from Rhenen
